cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MA, cs.CL, cs.RO

The paper introduces a novel learning-to-teach framework that improves scalability to complex environments by using deep representation for student policies and advising with more expressive extended action sequences over multiple levels of temporal abstraction. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), multi-agent systems (cs.MA), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and robotics (cs.RO).
